# Hybrid & QOL Modules

## Hybrid (Phase 4 + live-local)
- Format: `lunion-hybrid-v1` — PBKDF2 + AES-GCM via Web Crypto (`src/lib/crypto/passphrase.ts`)
- Passphrase **never** sent to the server; API exchanges plaintext slices over MFA only
- Routes: `GET/POST /api/hybrid/slice`; UI `/app/hybrid`
- Audit: `hybrid.export` / `hybrid.import`
- Encrypted slice in `localStorage` (`LocalHybridSliceAdapter`); when mode=`local` and unlocked, client grievance/bumping screens use `live-session` + `case-client` (not server adapters reading browser storage)
- Sync to hub is explicit POST; attachments remain hub-backed

## QOL (Phase 5+)
- Types: `src/types/qol.ts` — optional `bargainingUnitId` on snippets / marketplace
- Access helpers: `src/lib/qol/access.ts`
- ICS: `src/lib/calendar/ics.ts` (client download, grievance-scoped today) — see `.cursor/rules/calendar-meetings.mdc` for membership meeting scope
- Handoff: presidents/admins only (`canInitiateHandoff`); stamp active local (+ collection when set)
- Marketplace: same `unionId` only — never cross-union
- Stewards: assigned grievance R/W; bumping read-only; mobile read-only hides write CTAs
- Hub context switcher filters lists by active local/collection

## Do Not
- Auto-send email drafts or member communications
- Show handoff/share/delete CTAs the API will 403
- Cross-union marketplace or snippet reads
- Pretend server adapters read browser `localStorage` for hybrid live-local — client pages must branch
- Build a first-party member self-service portal under QOL
